From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kanaka Raju Nayana <kanaka.raju.nayana@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 17:05:45 +0530
Subject: drm/xe: manage drm show_fdinfo api availability

On Linux 5.15, Xe build fails because drm_show_fdinfo and the
drm_driver.show_fdinfo field are not available, causing undeclared
symbol and unknown struct member errors in xe_device.c.

The common fdinfo helper and show_fdinfo driver hook were introduced
in v6.5 kernel.

Resolved by adding an autotools probe for show_fdinfo support and
gating fdinfo assignments in xe_device.c.

Signed-off-by: Kanaka Raju Nayana <kanaka.raju.nayana@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_device.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_device.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_device.c
index 56c3df0..5aae170 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_device.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_device.c
@@ -384,7 +384,7 @@ static const struct file_operations xe_driver_fops = {
 	.read = drm_read,
 	.compat_ioctl = xe_drm_compat_ioctl,
 	.llseek = noop_llseek,
-#ifdef CONFIG_PROC_FS
+#if defined(CONFIG_PROC_FS) && !defined(BPM_DRM_SHOW_FDINFO_NOT_PRESENT)
 	.show_fdinfo = drm_show_fdinfo,
 #endif
 #ifndef BPM_FOP_UNSIGNED_OFFSET_NOT_PRESENT
@@ -407,7 +407,7 @@ static struct drm_driver driver = {
 
 	.dumb_create = xe_bo_dumb_create,
 	.dumb_map_offset = drm_gem_ttm_dumb_map_offset,
-#ifdef CONFIG_PROC_FS
+#if defined(CONFIG_PROC_FS) && !defined(BPM_DRM_SHOW_FDINFO_NOT_PRESENT)
 	.show_fdinfo = xe_drm_client_fdinfo,
 #endif
 	.ioctls = xe_ioctls,
